---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="About — rHACKham-le-Rouge">
  <Header />
  <main id="main-content" class="app-layout">
    <section id="hero">
      <div id="console-about"></div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script>
const PROMPT = "rHACKham@leRouge:~$ ";

const faq = [
  {
    q: "Why did I choose cybersecurity?",
    a: ["I started this journey for the wrong reasons.",
        "I was told there would be many job opportunities and high salaries.",
        "I later found out that things are not that simple...",
        "What started as curiosity and opportunity quickly became something more.",
        "I quickly developed a real passion for this field. I wanted to understand everything:",
        "how systems work, how vulnerabilities appear, and how attackers exploit them.",
        "Cybersecurity offers a constant challenge, where there is always something new to learn and understand.",
        "It also gave me a sense of purpose and usefulness.",
        "Helping to keep the people around me safer is truly rewarding.",
        "Maybe that's what it means to truly enjoy what you do.",
        "Not because it's easy, but because it feels worth it."]
  },
  {
    q: "What is my approach to learning?",
    a: ["I focus on hands-on practice.",
        "Instead of consuming purely theoretical content, I like to get my hands \"dirty\" with realistic scenarios.",
        "I learn best by doing, fixing or breaking things. Analyzing them, and understanding each step of the process.",
        "Discipline plays a key role in my progression.",
        "Consistency matters more than intensity."]
  },
  {
    q: "What do I actually do to improve my skills?",
    a: ["I started by enrolling in cybersecurity training programs.",
        "These gave me the foundational knowledge I needed to continue learning on my own across different platforms.",
        "Alongside this training, I completed most of the learning paths on TryHackMe, where I have solved more than 200 rooms and reached the top 1% of users.",
        "I then moved to Hack The Box Academy, where I am currently preparing for the CPTS certification.",
        "I work on it every day, progressing toward completing the full path and passing the final exam.",
        "This certification covers the entire penetration testing process, from reconnaissance to post-exploitation, and last but not least, reporting.",
        "I particularly enjoy this path because it goes deep into each topic.",
        "At the same time, I also work on Hack The Box labs and machines. These are a great way to improve my skills, as they are designed to replicate real-world scenarios.",
        "The machines are very diverse and expose me to different technologies and exploitation techniques.",
        "I am working my way toward the \"Pro Hacker\" rank.",
        "Pro Labs are even closer to real-world pentesting.",
        "They require understanding an entire network, including how multiple machines with different operating systems interact with each other. You need to pivot between hosts to successfully complete them.",
        "I also participate in CTF challenges to improve my problem-solving skills.",
        "I tend to prefer OSINT CTFs. In more traditional CTFs, it has become common to compete against teams (ab)using AI agents, which, in my opinion, goes against the spirit of these challenges.",
        "OSINT investigations are, for now, less affected by this (for now...).",
        "My goal is not just to solve challenges, but to deeply understand how and why each technique works."]
  },
  {
    q: "Why cyber defense and why ESNA?",
    a: ["As I work toward my goal of becoming a cybersecurity expert, I realized that self-learning alone is not enough, structure and guidance are essential.",
        "I want to be able to design and build cybersecurity solutions from the ground up, adapted to a wide range of clients.",
        "This is exactly what this engineering degree aims to achieve.",
        "The program provides a comprehensive and practical approach to cybersecurity, combining offensive and defensive topics such as penetration testing, digital forensics, secure development, system and network security, as well as hands-on projects over two years.",
        "Why ESNA?",
        "From the moment I first heard about ESNA, I knew it was the logical choice to continue my academic journey.",
        "The school clearly strives for excellence, and it shows in its results. It is currently ranked number one worldwide in the Hack The Box university rankings, and its track record speaks for itself.",
        "I also had the opportunity to meet some of the teachers and students, which only confirmed that this is the right environment for me to grow and reach my goals."]
  },
  {
    q: "What are my goals?",
    a: ["My short-term goals are to be fully prepared for my first apprenticeship, where I can be immediately useful and contribute effectively to the team, while paving the way to start my engineering diploma at ESNA.",
        "At the same time, I am focused on completing the CPTS certification and continuing to strengthen my practical skills through platforms like Hack The Box.",
        "In the mid-term, I aim to obtain the Cyber Defense Engineer diploma while continuing to work on personal projects and certifications such as OSCP or BSCP in my free time.",
        "I also plan to identify a specialization that will be both impactful for my career and engaging in daily work, allowing me to apply my offensive and defensive expertise in real-world environments.",
        "In the long term, my goal is to become a cybersecurity expert capable of understanding complex systems, identifying vulnerabilities, and delivering tailored security solutions that address each client's unique challenges.",
        "My journey is guided by a desire to develop practical skills, contribute to meaningful projects, and become a trusted cybersecurity expert for both clients and teams."]
  },
  {
    q: "Why this blog?",
    a: ["This blog is not meant to provide advanced technical content for experienced cybersecurity professionals. I am still building my expertise.",
        "Instead, it serves as a way to present myself in more detail than a traditional CV allows.",
        "Through this blog, I aim to showcase my skills in report writing, my understanding of different vulnerabilities, and the progress I am making in my cybersecurity journey.",
        "It is both a personal record of my growth and a window for recruiters to see my capabilities, approach, skills and weaknesses.",
        "If it helps others along the way, even better."]
  },
];

function renderConsole() {
  const consoleEl = document.getElementById("console-about");
  if (!consoleEl) return;
  if (consoleEl.dataset.rendered === "true") return;
  consoleEl.dataset.rendered = "true";
  consoleEl.innerHTML = "";

  function addDiv(html: string, color?: string): HTMLDivElement {
    const div = document.createElement("div");
    div.innerHTML = html;
    if (color) div.style.color = color;
    consoleEl.appendChild(div);
    return div;
  }

  function addText(text: string, color?: string): HTMLDivElement {
    const div = document.createElement("div");
    div.textContent = text;
    if (color) div.style.color = color;
    consoleEl.appendChild(div);
    return div;
  }

  function addEmpty() {
    const div = document.createElement("div");
    div.innerHTML = "&nbsp;";
    consoleEl.appendChild(div);
  }

  function addPromptCommand(command: string) {
    addDiv(`<span class="prompt-text">${PROMPT}</span>${command}`);
  }

  function addTitle(text: string) {
    addDiv(`<span style="font-size:22px;letter-spacing:6px;color:#00ff41;font-weight:bold;">${text}</span>`);
  }

  // --- About Me ---
  addPromptCommand("cat about.txt");
  addEmpty();
  addTitle("[ About Me ]");
  addEmpty();

  const aboutLines = [
    "I didn't get into cybersecurity by following a clear path.",
    "With no academic background or prior skills in this field,",
    "I had to build everything from the ground up, step by step,",
    "through challenges, successes (sometimes failures),",
    "and most importantly, PERSISTENCE.",
    "",
    "My goal is to develop strong and well-rounded skills that allow",
    "me to understand how computer systems are attacked,",
    "and how to protect them effectively.",
    "",
    "Beyond the technical aspect, I also care about the human side",
    "of cybersecurity. I want to help people around me feel safer",
    "when using their devices and browsing the internet.",
    "Many people don't realize how exposed they are.",
    "Some don't know how to protect themselves, while others",
    "simply believe that \"it only happens to others.\"",
    "",
    "Cybersecurity is not just about systems; it's about awareness,",
    "habits, and responsibility. And I feel it is my duty to help",
    "protect those who can't protect themselves.",
  ];

  aboutLines.forEach(line => {
    if (line === "") addEmpty();
    else addText(line, "#e0e0e0");
  });

  // --- Q&A ---
  addEmpty();
  addPromptCommand("Q&A --help");
  addEmpty();
  addTitle("[ Questions & Answers ]");
  addEmpty();

  faq.forEach((item) => {
    const wrapper = document.createElement("div");
    wrapper.style.marginBottom = "4px";

    const question = document.createElement("div");
    question.style.color = "#00ff41";
    question.style.cursor = "pointer";
    question.style.userSelect = "none";
    question.innerHTML = `<span style="color:#555;">▶</span> ${item.q}`;

    const answer = document.createElement("div");
    answer.style.display = "none";
    answer.style.color = "#e0e0e0";
    answer.style.paddingLeft = "1.5rem";
    answer.style.marginTop = "4px";
    answer.style.marginBottom = "8px";

    item.a.forEach(line => {
      const p = document.createElement("div");
      p.textContent = line;
      answer.appendChild(p);
    });

    question.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const isOpen = answer.style.display !== "none";
      answer.style.display = isOpen ? "none" : "block";
      const arrow = question.querySelector("span");
      if (arrow) arrow.textContent = isOpen ? "▶" : "▼";
    });

    wrapper.appendChild(question);
    wrapper.appendChild(answer);
    consoleEl.appendChild(wrapper);
  });

  // --- Contact ---
  addEmpty();
  addPromptCommand("ls /contact");
  addEmpty();
  addTitle("[ Let's Connect ]");
  addEmpty();

  [
    "If you are on a similar path, working on CTFs,",
    "or building your skills in cybersecurity, feel free to reach out.",
    "Learning is better when it is shared.",
  ].forEach(line => addText(line, "#e0e0e0"));

  addEmpty();

  addDiv(`
    <div style="color:#e0e0e0;">
      <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/rHACKham-leRouge" target="_blank">github.com/rHACKham-leRouge</a></div>
      <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://app.hackthebox.com/public/users/2203617" target="_blank">hackthebox.com → rHACKham-leRouge</a></div>
      <div>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="mailto:rh4ck4m_l3_r0uge@proton.me">rh4ck4m_l3_r0uge@proton.me</a></div>
    </div>
  `);

  addEmpty();

  const lastLine = addDiv(`<span class="prompt-text">${PROMPT}</span>`);
  const cursor = document.createElement("span");
  cursor.className = "cursor";
  cursor.textContent = "█";
  lastLine.appendChild(cursor);
}

document.addEventListener("astro:page-load", renderConsole);
document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", renderConsole);
if (document.readyState !== "loading") renderConsole();
</script>

<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Share+Tech+Mono&display=swap');

  :global(body), :global(html) {
    background: #0a0a0a !important;
  }

  :global(header) {
    background: #0a0a0a !important;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a1a !important;
    box-shadow: none !important;
  }

  :global(header *) { color: #00ff41 !important; }
  :global(header svg), :global(header svg *) {
    stroke: #00ff41 !important;
    fill: none !important;
  }

  :global(footer) {
    background: #0a0a0a !important;
    border-top: 1px solid #1a1a1a !important;
  }
  :global(footer *) { color: #444 !important; }
  :global(footer a) { color: #00c832 !important; }

  :global(:root) { --background: #0a0a0a !important; }

  #hero {
    min-height: calc(100vh - 120px);
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
  }

  #console-about {
    font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #00ff41;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  #console-about .prompt-text { color: #00c832; }

  #console-about a {
    color: #00ff41;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #004400;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  #console-about a:hover { color: #fff; }

  :global(.cursor) { animation: blink 1s step-end infinite; }

  @keyframes blink {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0; }
  }
</style>